text:
In the poor neighborhoods of the city these street vendors are a familiar sight. From the miniature wagon its owner is selling ice cream, frankfurters, and candy. Bush and Clinton Streets, Brooklyn.

P. L. Sperr, photographer
June 9, 1938.
title: Occupations - Peddlers - Food - [Brooklyn].

folder: Clinton Street & Bush Street, Brooklyn, NY
text:
Clinton Street, north from Bush Street, showing (left) the fenced-off area on the west side of the street where the Red Hook Houses, a housing center sponsored by the New York City Housing Authority, was erected.

P. L. Sperr
April 9, 1939
